ZCZC GE02
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SATURDAY TO TUESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 272300 UTC
ON SATURDAY EVENING HIGH PRESSURE OVER SHANNON 1025 WILL EXTEND A RIDGE
N AND E ACROSS THE BRITISH ISLES. LOW PRESSURE OVER SCANDINAVIA 998 WILL
STEADILY FILL AS THE HIGH PRESSURE CENTRE SLWY MIGRATES E. THE HIGH PRESSURE
WILL CONTINUE TO EXTEND ITS RIDGE FM THE AZORES TOWARD NORWAY COVERING THE
ENTIRETY OF BRITAIN AND THE NORWEGIAN BASIN ON SUNDAY. BY MONDAY AFTERNOON
THE HIGH PRESSURE WILL BE CENTRED OVER DOGGER 1022. LOW PRESSURE WILL DEVELOP
IN THE W 998 MOV INTO SHANNON DURING THE SAME PERIOD. THIS LOW PRESSURE
WILL CONTINUE TO DISPLACE THE HIGH PRESSURE INTO SCANDINAVIA BY TUESDAY
MORNING. STRG WINDS ARE EXP ACROSS THE N SEA THOUGH SATURDAY NIGHT AND THE
INITIAL PART OF SUNDAY MORNING. STRG WINDS MAY RETURN ON MONDAY NIGHT AND
TUESDAY MORNING ACROSS FAIR ISLE AND VIKING WITH NEAR GALES POSS. NO FURTHER
